6) Step 6 - Database Design

Users Collection
User
{
  name
  email
  password
  role
}

Complaints Collection
Complaint
{
  userId
  complaintText
  category
  priority
  department
  status
  createdAt
}

7) Step 7 - Complaint Submission Flow

User submits complaint:

User -> Frontend Form -> Backend API -> Database

Example complaint:

Street light not working near bus stop

8) Step 8 - AI Complaint Classification

Create Python AI model

Folder:

ai-model
|
|-- train_model.py
|-- predict.py
`-- complaint_model.pkl

AI Pipeline
Complaint Text
      |
      v
Text Cleaning
      |
      v
TF-IDF Vectorization
      |
      v
Machine Learning Model
(Logistic Regression)
      |
      v
Predicted Category

Example output:

Input:
Garbage not collected

Output:
Category -> Sanitation
Priority -> Medium
Department -> Cleaning

9) Step 9 - Connect AI with Backend

Backend sends complaint text to Python model.

Flow:

Frontend
   |
   v
Node.js Backend
   |
   v
Python AI API
   |
   v
Prediction
   |
   v
Save in MongoDB

Example response:

{
  category: "Sanitation",
  priority: "Medium"
}

10) Step 10 - Admin Dashboard

Admin can see:
- Total complaints
- Complaints by category
- Resolved complaints
- Pending complaints

Charts:
- Pie chart
- Bar chart
- Line graph

11) Step 11 - Complaint Status System

Status types:
- Submitted
- Under Review
- In Progress
- Resolved
- Closed

Admin updates complaint status.

12) Step 12 - AI Analytics

Advanced dashboard features:
- Most common complaint category
- Complaint trends
- Department performance
- Resolution time

13) Step 13 - Extra Advanced Features

To make the project very impressive:

1) Sentiment Analysis

Detect angry complaints.

Example:

Very poor service, water leaking everywhere!

Priority -> High

2) Image Complaint Detection

User uploads image:

Example:
- pothole
- garbage

AI detects issue using computer vision.

3) Chatbot Support

User asks:

What is my complaint status?

AI chatbot replies.

